Label: Moco
Comment: molybdenum, cofactor for XDH and ADO enzymes

Label: 6-oxopyrimidine (M1)
Comment: Oxidize version of auglurant, N-(5-fluoropyridin-2-yl)-6-methyl-4-((6-oxo)1,6-dihydropyrimidin-5-yloxy)picolinamide, aka VU0652922; structure drawn based on Fig. 1 [PMID:28939686]

Label: 5-PRA
Comment: ChEBI for 5-phospho-β-D-ribosylamine that is used in the conversion from 5-PRA to GAR. The ChEBI for 5-PRA in the conversion from PRPP to 5-PRA is 58089 (5-phospho-D-ribosylamine)

Label: Moco (inactive)
Comment: 'In addition to the dithiolene sulfurs of the pterin moiety and two oxo groups, the molybdenum atom of Moco needs the addition of a terminal inorganic sulfur to provide enzyme activity to these enzymes (55). This final step is catalyzed by the Moco sulfurase protein (ABA3 in plants and HMCS in humans) ' [PMID:23539623]. HMCS is an alternative name for MOCOS (in UniProt, https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/Q96EN8/entry)

Label: GAR
Comment: ChEBI identifier will be replaced and updated by RHEA end of July

Label: Moco (active)
Comment: 'In addition to the dithiolene sulfurs of the pterin moiety and two oxo groups, the molybdenum atom of Moco needs the addition of a terminal inorganic sulfur to provide enzyme activity to these enzymes (55). This final step is catalyzed by the Moco sulfurase protein (ABA3 in plants and HMCS in humans) ' [PMID:23539623]. HMCS is an alternative name for MOCOS (in UniProt, https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/Q96EN8/entry)

Label: AO
Comment: Aldehyde oxidase (AO) is a metabolizing enzyme, located in the cytosolic compartment of tissues in many organisms. AO catalyzes the oxidation of aldehydes into carboxylic acid, and in addition, catalyzes the hydrozylation of some heterocycles.[1] It can also catalyze the oxidation of both cytochrome P450 (CYP450) and monoamine oxidase (MAO) intermediate products. AO plays a very important role in the metabolization of numerous drugs.</br>'Aldehyde oxidase (AO) and xanthine oxidase (XO) belong to a family of molybdo-flavoenzymes that catalyze the oxidation of nitrogen-containing aromatic heterocycles.' [PMID:28939686]

Label: XO
Comment: aka Xanthine oxidase; 'Aldehyde oxidase (AO) and xanthine oxidase (XO) belong to a family of molybdo-flavoenzymes that catalyze the oxidation of nitrogen-containing aromatic heterocycles.' [PMID:28939686]
